      <h1 class='title'>Home Reversion Plans</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 11 November 2003 vol 413 c17WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_17ws' title='Col. 17WS &mdash; HC Deb 11 November 2003 vol 413 c17WS' name='column_17ws' href='#column_17ws' rel='bookmark'>17WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0413P2_20031111_CWS_5'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-dawn-primarolo' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0413P2_20031111_CWS_5' title='Link to this speech by Ms Dawn Primarolo' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-dawn-primarolo" title="Ms Dawn Primarolo">The Paymaster General (Dawn Primarolo)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The Treasury is today publishing a consultation document seeking evidence to inform an in-depth analysis of the costs and benefits of regulation by the Financial Services Authority (FSA) of home reversion plans. Copies of the document have been placed in the Library. Responses to the consultation are requested by 13 February 2004.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
